Graph:Chart\n| type = rect\n| width = 800\n| colors = orange\n| xAxisTitle = Date\n| xAxisAngle = -40\n| x = 26 Feb, 27 Feb, 28 Feb, 29 Feb, 1 Mar, 2 Mar, 3 Mar, 4 Mar, 5 Mar, 6 Mar, 7 Mar, 8 Mar, 9 Mar, 10 Mar, 11 Mar, 12 Mar, 13 Mar, 14 Mar, 15 Mar, 16 Mar, 17 Mar, 18 Mar, 19 Mar, 20 Mar, 21 Mar, 22 Mar, 23 Mar, 24 Mar, 25 Mar, 26 Mar, 27 Mar, 28 Mar, 29 Mar, 30 Mar, 31 Mar, 1 Apr\n| yAxisTitle = No. of new tested\n| y1 = 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 475, 0, 0, 182, 77, 0, 75, 139, 231, 0, 742, 624, 384, 276, 503, 442, 520, 303, 3311, 631, 1052, 1256, 1401, 1842, 1532, 1455, 2210, 1797, 1643, 1551, 1955\n| legend=Legend\n| showValues=offset:2\n| y1Title = Tested per day\n| yGrid = | xGrid = \n}}\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Romania medical cases}}\nAs of 18 March, a plurality (29%) of COVID-19 cases were people between the ages of 40 and 49. Of the patients, 51% are women, 44% are men, and children \u2013 5%.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hotnews.ro/stiri-coronavirus-23734261-infografic-varste-romanii-care-imbolnavit-covid-19-varsta-medie-pacientilor-41-ani.htm |title=INFOGRAFIC Ce v\u00e2rste au rom\u00e2nii care s-au \u00eemboln\u0103vit de COVID-19. V\u00e2rsta medie a pacien\u021bilor - 41 de ani |website=HotNews.ro |author=H., I. |date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Impact ==\n=== Economy ===\n[[File:Carrefour Brasov shelves, Covid.jpg|thumb|200px|Empty shelves in a [[Bra\u0219ov]] supermarket after [[panic buying]]]]\nDuring the second week of March, the [[Bucharest Stock Exchange]] recorded losses on all five trading sessions, the main index BET collapsing with 17.6%, the steepest decline since December 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.zf.ro/burse-fonduri-mutuale/saptamana-de-cosmar-pentru-bursa-romaneasca-prabusire-de-17-6-inca-nu-stim-daca-socul-economic-va-dura-1-luna-2-luni-sau-mai-mult-18982027 |title=S\u0103pt\u0103m\u00e2na de co\u0219mar pentru bursa rom\u00e2neasc\u0103: pr\u0103bu\u0219ire de 17,6%. \"\u00cenc\u0103 nu \u0219tim dac\u0103 \u0219ocul economic va dura 1 lun\u0103, 2 luni, sau mai mult\" |website=Ziarul Financiar |author=Popescu, Liviu |date=14 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, the [[National Bank of Romania]] announced a reference rate of 4.8242 [[Romanian leu|lei]]/[[euro]], a historical maximum for the single European currency against the leu.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://incont.stirileprotv.ro/cursuri/moneda-unica-marcheaza-un-nou-maxim-istoric-in-raport-cu-leul-c-curs-a-anuntat-bnr-pentru-euro.html |title=Moneda unic\u0103 marcheaz\u0103 un nou maxim istoric \u00een raport cu leul. Ce curs a anun\u021bat BNR pentru euro |website=inCont.ro |date=16 March 2020}}</ref> The leu continued its depreciation, reaching a maximum of 4.8448 lei/euro on 17 March.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.economica.net/curs-bnr-azi-17-martie-2020-leu-euro-dolar-franc-elvetian-curs-valutar-interbancar-robor-aur_181227.html |title=A doua zi consecutiv\u0103 \u00een care leul atinge minimul istoric \u00een fa\u021ba euro. Curs BNR 17.03.2020: 4,8448 lei/euro |website=Economica.net |date=17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Education ===\nOn 9 March, interim Prime-minister [[Ludovic Orban]] announced the closure of all schools between 11 and 22 March. The measure targets all kindergartens, primary, secondary and high schools in Romania, both public and private, according to Education Minister {{ill|Monica Anisie|ro}}.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.romania-insider.com/romania-closes-schools-coronavirus-march-2020 |title=Update: Romania closes all schools to fight coronavirus outbreak |website=Romania-Insider.com |date=9 March 2020}}</ref> The decision affects 3.5 million students.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/bucurestenii-inchiderea-scolilor-coronavirus-2909216 |title=Cum se adapteaz\u0103 bucure\u0219tenii la \u00eenchiderea \u0219colilor \u0219i ce p\u0103rere au despre \u00eenmul\u021birea cazurilor de coronavirus |website=Libertatea |last1=Stanciu |first1=Daniel |last2=Nistor |first2=Cosmin |last3=Capoeanu |first3=George |date=11 March 2020}}</ref> Likewise, several universities in the major student centres suspended their courses. These include the [[University of Bucharest]], the [[Bucharest Academy of Economic Studies]], the [[Politehnica University of Bucharest]], the [[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University]], the [[West University of Timi\u0219oara]], etc.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.libertatea.ro/stiri/universitatea-bucuresti-isi-suspenda-cursurile-2908415 |title=UPDATE. Universitatea din Bucure\u0219ti \u0219i ASE \u00ee\u0219i suspend\u0103 cursurile p\u00e2n\u0103 la sf\u00e2r\u0219itul lunii |website=Libertatea |author=Radu, Cristina |date=11 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mediafax.ro/coronavirus/cea-mai-mare-universitate-din-tara-ubb-suspenda-cursurile-pana-in-22-martie-18959559 |title=Cea mai mare universitate din \u021bar\u0103, UBB, suspend\u0103 cursurile p\u00e2n\u0103 \u00een 22 martie |website=Mediafax |author=M\u0103gr\u0103dean, Vasile |date=10 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pressalert.ro/2020/03/se-suspenda-cursurile-si-la-universitatea-de-vest-din-timisoara-din-cauza-coronavirus/ |title=Se suspend\u0103 cursurile \u0219i la Universitatea de Vest din Timi\u0219oara, din cauza COVID 19 |website=pressalert.ro |author=M\u00ee\u021b, Adriana |date=11 March 2020}}</ref> Furthermore, Anisie announced that, as a measure of prevention and control of the illnesses with COVID-19 in schools, the Ministry of Education had decided to suspend all county and regional school olympiads, as well as sports competitions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.agerpres.ro/educatie-stiinta/2020/03/09/mec-olimpiadele-scolare-judetene-si-regionale-precum-si-concursurile-sportive-suspendate--462247|title=MEC: Olimpiadele \u015fcolare jude\u0163ene \u015fi regionale, precum \u015fi concursurile sportive - suspendate|last=AGERPRES|website=www.agerpres.ro|language=ro|access-date=2020-03-15}}</ref>\n\nThe show ''Tele\u0219coal\u0103'' (Teleschool), announced by the Ministry of Education and dedicated to the students who stay at home during the period when the schools are closed, started on [[TVR 2]] on 16 March, at 9 a.m. Students can follow, from Monday to Friday, [[mathematics]], [[Romanian language|Romanian]], [[biology]], [[history]] and [[geography]] classes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mbl.hotnews.ro/stire/23718809|title=TVR: Tele\u0219coala pentru elevii care stau acas\u0103 \u00eencepe pe 16 martie - Hotnews Mobile|website=mbl.hotnews.ro|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mobile.hotnews.ro/stire/23727012|title=Tele\u0218coala a fost LIVE VIDEO pe ecrane \u0219i pe site-ul TVR+. ORARUL complet al cursurilor din prima s\u0103pt\u0103m\u00e2n\u0103 - Hotnews Mobile|website=mobile.hotnews.ro|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March, Anisie announced that schools would remain closed while the state of emergency was in place, at least until after [[Easter]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.digi24.ro/stiri/actualitate/educatie/ministrul-educatiei-scolile-raman-inchise-pana-dupa-paste-cat-e-anuntata-starea-de-urgenta-1276054|title=Ministrul Educa\u021biei: \u0218colile r\u0103m\u00e2n \u00eenchise p\u00e2n\u0103 dup\u0103 Pa\u0219te, c\u00e2t e anun\u021bat\u0103 starea de urgen\u021b\u0103|website=www.digi24.ro|language=ro|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mbl.hotnews.ro/stire/23726531|title=Monica Anisie, ministrul Educa\u021biei: \u0218colile r\u0103m\u00e2n \u00eenchise p\u00e2n\u0103 dup\u0103 Pa\u0219te, c\u00e2t e anun\u021bat\u0103 starea de urgen\u021b\u0103 - Hotnews Mobile|website=mbl.hotnews.ro|access-date=2020-03-21}}</ref>\n\n=== Sports ===\nThe [[Romanian Football Federation]] and the [[Romanian Handball Federation]] decided to suspend all matches until 31 March.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.digisport.ro/fotbal/pandemia-de-coronavirus-a-pus-lacat-pe-fotbalul-romanesc-frf-a-suspendat-toate-meciurile-810522 |title=Pandemia de coronavirus a pus \"lac\u0103t\" pe fotbalul rom\u00e2nesc! FRF a suspendat toate meciurile |website=Digi Sport |date=12 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://realitateasportiva.net/frh-anunta-ca-toate-competitiile-pe-plan-intern-au-fost-suspendate/ |title=FRH anun\u021b\u0103 c\u0103 toate competi\u021biile pe plan intern au fost suspendate |website=Realitatea Sportiv\u0103 |author=Bulgakov, Kadi |date=13 March 2020}}</ref> The rugby match between Romania and Belgium, to be held in [[Boto\u0219ani]] on 14 March, was postponed by [[Rugby Europe]].<ref name=\"ziare\" /> The [[IWF Junior World Weightlifting Championships]] in [[Bucharest]], scheduled for 14\u201321 March, have been cancelled.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://realitateasportiva.net/o-competitie-sportiva-din-romania-anulata-din-cauza-epidemiei-de-coronavirus/ |title=O competi\u021bie sportiv\u0103 din Rom\u00e2nia, anulat\u0103 din cauza epidemiei de coronavirus |website=Realitatea Sportiv\u0103 |author=Iona\u0219cu, Andrei |date=2 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/#countries Confirmed cases and deaths by country, territory, or conveyance] (worldometer)\n* [https://instnsp.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/5eced796595b4ee585bcdba03e30c127 Interactive map with confirmed cases, people in quarantine, isolated people, etc.] (ArcGIS)\n* [https://covid19.geo-spatial.org/dashboard/main Maps and statistics on the situation of COVID-19 pandemic in Romania] (geo-spatial.org)\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|Romania]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in Romania]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in Europe]]\n[[Category:2020 in Romania]]\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|Romania]]\n", "name_user": "Sidneysage", "label": "safe", "comment": "Updated information, added links", "url_page": "